lets it transitioned to an enterprise software and services company under ceo john s chen its products are used worldwide by various businesses car makers and government agencies and include the athoc crisis communications platform the qnx realtime operating system and blackberry uem an endpoint management platform blackberry was founded in  as research in motion by mike lazaridis and douglas fregin fregin retired from the company in  in  lazaridis hired jim balsillie and lazaridis and balsillie served as coceos until january   in november  john s chen took over as ceo his initial strategy was to subcontract manufacturing to foxconn and to focus on software technology currently his strategy includes forming licensing partnerships with device manufacturers such as tcl communication and unifying blackberry’s software portfolio contents  history  early years and growth –  global expansion and competition –  primary competition  strategic changes and restructuring –present  blackberry   premwatsafairfax deal  john chen joins blackberry  software transition present  strategic acquisitions  hardware licensing partnerships  cybersecurity consulting  blackberry secure  financials  organizational changes  leadership changes  workforce reductions  stock fluctuations  rumored samsung buyout  mobile os transition  blackberry os java  blackberry tablet os qnx  blackberry  qnx  android  acquisitions  slipstream data inc  certicom  dash navigation  torch mobile  dataviz  viigo  qnx  the astonishing tribe  jaycut  tungleme  newbay  scoreloop  gist  scroon  movirtu  secusmart  watchdox  athoc  good technology  encription  software  blackberry unified endpoint manager uem  blackberry dynamics formerly good dynamics  blackberry workspaces formerly watchdox  blackberry fa formerly strong authentication  bbm enterprise  blackberry athoc  secusuite  blackberry qnx  patent litigation  glenayre electronics  good technologies  handspring  ntp  xerox  visto  motorola  eatoni  mformation  qua